# Next.js Data Patterns

## Database Access (db/queries)

All data fetching and mutations must go through helper functions in the **db/queries** directory. Do not use `db` (Drizzle) directly in Server Components, Server Actions, or route handlers.

- **Queries (reads)**: Define in `db/queries/` (e.g. `getGroup`, `getGroups`, `getEvent`). Server Components and Server Actions call these for data fetching.
- **Mutations (writes)**: Define in `db/queries/` (e.g. `createGroup`, `updateEvent`, `deleteGroup`). Server Actions handle auth and Zod validation, then call these helpers and run revalidation.

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: db/queries/groups.ts – query helper
import { db } from '@/db';
import { groupsTable } from '@/db/schema';
import { eq } from 'drizzle-orm';

export async function getGroup(id: string) {
  const [group] = await db.select().from(groupsTable).where(eq(groupsTable.id, id));
  return group ?? null;
}

// ✅ CORRECT: db/queries/groups.ts – mutation helper
export async function insertGroup(data: { name: string; description: string; city: string; ownerId: string }) {
  await db.insert(groupsTable).values(data);
}

// ❌ WRONG: Using db directly in a Server Component or Server Action
export default async function Page() {
  const groups = await db.select().from(groupsTable); // Use getGroups() from db/queries instead
  return <div>...</div>;
}
```

## Server Actions

Server Actions validate input with Zod, enforce auth, call mutation helpers from **db/queries**, then revalidate.

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: actions/groups.ts – calls db/queries, validates, revalidates
import { auth } from '@clerk/nextjs/server';
import { revalidatePath } from 'next/cache';
import { z } from 'zod';
import { insertGroup } from '@/db/queries/groups';

const createGroupSchema = z.object({
  name: z.string().min(1),
  description: z.string(),
  city: z.string().min(1),
});

type CreateGroupInput = z.infer<typeof createGroupSchema>;

export async function createGroup(input: CreateGroupInput) {
  const { userId } = await auth();
  if (!userId) throw new Error('Unauthorized');

  const validated = createGroupSchema.parse(input);
  await insertGroup({ ...validated, ownerId: userId });
  revalidatePath('/groups');
}

// ❌ WRONG: Using FormData as type, no validation
export async function createGroup(formData: FormData) {
  const name = formData.get('name');
  await db.insert(groupsTable).values({ name });
}
```

## Data Validation

All data validation must use **Zod schemas**. Define schemas before your Server Actions and validate all input.

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Zod validation
import { z } from 'zod';

const updateEventSchema = z.object({
  id: z.string().uuid(),
  title: z.string().min(3).max(100),
  date: z.date(),
  maxAttendees: z.number().int().positive().optional(),
});

type UpdateEventInput = z.infer<typeof updateEventSchema>;

export async function updateEvent(input: UpdateEventInput) {
  const validated = updateEventSchema.parse(input);
  await updateEventById(validated); // from db/queries/events
}

// ❌ WRONG: No validation, or using db directly
export async function updateEvent(input: any) {
  await db.update(eventsTable).set(input);
}
```

## TypeScript Types for Server Actions

Server Action parameters must use proper TypeScript types derived from Zod schemas. **Never use `FormData` as the parameter type.**

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT: Proper TypeScript type from Zod
const deleteGroupSchema = z.object({
  groupId: z.string(),
});

type DeleteGroupInput = z.infer<typeof deleteGroupSchema>;

export async function deleteGroup(input: DeleteGroupInput) {
  const validated = deleteGroupSchema.parse(input);
  await deleteGroupById(validated.groupId); // from db/queries/groups
}

// ❌ WRONG: Using FormData as parameter type
export async function deleteGroup(formData: FormData) {
  const groupId = formData.get('groupId');
  // ... implementation
}
```

## Client Component Integration

Client Components should call Server Actions and receive data as props from Server Components.

```typescript
// Server Component (page.tsx) – data via db/queries
import { notFound } from 'next/navigation';
import { getGroup } from '@/db/queries/groups';

export default async function GroupPage({ params }: { params: { id: string } }) {
  const group = await getGroup(params.id);
  if (!group) notFound();
  return <GroupDetails group={group} />;
}

// Client Component (GroupDetails.tsx)
'use client';
import { deleteGroup } from '@/actions/groups';

export function GroupDetails({ group }: { group: Group }) {
  const handleDelete = async () => {
    await deleteGroup({ groupId: group.id });
  };
  
  return <button onClick={handleDelete}>Delete</button>;
}
```

## Important Reminders

- **db/queries**: All reads and writes go through helper functions in `db/queries/`. No direct `db` usage in pages, actions, or route handlers.
- **Server Components**: Fetch data only by calling query helpers from `db/queries/` (e.g. `getGroup`, `getGroups`).
- **Server Actions**: Validate with Zod, enforce auth, call mutation helpers from `db/queries/`, then call `revalidatePath()` or `revalidateTag()`.
- **Zod Schemas**: Define and validate all Server Action inputs.
- **Type Safety**: Use `z.infer<typeof schema>` for TypeScript types.
- **No FormData Types**: Use proper TypeScript types from Zod schemas for action parameters.
- **Revalidation**: Call `revalidatePath()` or `revalidateTag()` after mutations to update cached data.
